snippet: The real effects of the United States’ sanctions on Russia over its intervention in Ukraine appear to be more psychological than tangible, economic specialists say.
abstract: Economic specialists say real effect of United States sanctions on Russia over its intervention in Ukraine appear to be more psychological than tangible; note both Russian ruble and stock markets are slightly stronger than they were before the first sanctions were announced.

byline.original: By PETER BAKER and ANDREW E. KRAMER
byline.contributor: Peter Baker reported from Washington, and Andrew E. Kramer from Moscow. Danny Hakim contributed reporting from London, and Andrew W. Lehren and Natalia V. Osipova from New York.

lead_paragraph: The real effects of the United States’ sanctions on Russia over its intervention in Ukraine appear to be more psychological than tangible, economic specialists say.

headline.main: So Far, U.S. Sanctions Over Ukraine May Be Inflicting Only Limited Pain on Russia
headline.print_headline: So Far, U.S. Sanctions Over Ukraine May Be Inflicting Only Limited Pain on Russia
